Meanwhile, EIS offers an additional method for assessing the charge transfer kinetics of the electrocatalyst. As depicted in Fig. 4e, CQDs-Cu-Mo-Ni3S2@NF displays an exceptionally low charge transfer resistance (R

                        ct
                     ) value of 1.2 Ω, in stark contrast to CQDs-Mo-Ni3S2@NF (5.5 Ω), CQDs-Cu-Ni3S2@NF (6.6 Ω), CQDs-Ni3S2@NF (9.5 Ω) and NF (10 Ω) at the same overpotential of 170 mV. Therefore, CQDs-Cu-Mo-Ni3S2@NF exhibits enhanced charge transfer performance and superior electrical conductivity during the HER process, which can be attributed to its unique morphology and electron transfer interactions among multiple interfaces. These findings align well with the results obtained from the Tafel analysis.
